                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/64: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-18T09:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1921—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. President Meléndez informs me that he is negotiating a loan of $10,000,000
                    through Bloom Brothers, an American firm New York, to be guaranteed by a
                    percentage of the customhouse receipts. The lenders will appoint a controller of
                    the customhouses of the Republic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Arnold</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
